author: Anonym
title: Ukraine: “Putin has no limit, France will have no limit in its support” in kyiv, assures Sylvain Maillard - Teller Report
text: Yanis Darras 8:59 a.m., March 8, 2024 Sylvain Maillard, president of the Renaissance group in the National Assembly and deputy for Paris, was the guest of the Grande Interview Europe 1-CNews. At the microphone of Romain Desarbres, he returned to the Ukrainian conflict and assured that “France will have no limit in its support for Ukraine”. The war does not end in Ukraine. Two years after the start of the Russian invasion of Ukrainian territory, the conflict has become bogged down. Both armies are struggling to advance, while aid to kyiv remains more fragile than ever. Guest on the set of La Grande interview Europe 1-CNews, the president of the Renaissance group in the National Assembly and member of parliament for Paris, Sylvain Maillard, does not hide France's determination to continue its support for the Ukrainian state. “Putin has no limits in his attacks. France will have no limits in its support for Ukraine. It is very clear. The President of the Republic has said so,” he insists. at the microphone of Romain Desarbres. >>More information to follow >>More information to follow
